snippet: Dr. Hambrick founded the American Skin Association in 1987 with two colleagues and was its president from its inception to his death.
abstract: Dr George Hambrick, dermatologist who helped establish the American Skin Association, dies at age 91.
lead_paragraph: Dr. Hambrick founded the American Skin Association in 1987 with two colleagues and was its president from its inception to his death.

headline.main: George Hambrick, 91, Leader in Dermatology, Dies
